fields.description:
Navigating the network of knowledge: mining quotations from massive-scale digital libraries of books

Abstract: Scanning books, magazines, and newspapers is widespread because people believe a great deal of the world's information still resides off-line. In general after works are scanned they are indexed for search and processed to add links. In this talk I will describe a new approach to automatically add links by mining repeated passages. This technique connects elements that are semantically rich, so strong relations are made. Moreover, link targets point within rather than to the entire work, facilitating navigation. Our system has been run on a digital library of over 1 million books (Google Book Search), has been used by thousands of people, and has generated the world's largest collection of quotations. I will also present a follow-on project based on the theory that authors copy passages from book to book because these quotations capture an idea particularly well: Jefferson on liberty; Stanton on women's rights; and Gibson on cyberpunk. These projects suggest that mining quotations for links and ideas is an important mechanism for understanding the knowledge contained in books. (This work is in collaboration with Okan Kolak, Google Research and Google Book Search.)

Bio: Bill Schilit is part of the Google research team and an adopted member of the Book Search group. Before joining Google, Bill was co-director of the Intel Research lab in Seattle, managed digital library and mobile computing research at Fuji-Xerox (FXPAL), worked on distributed computing at AT&T's Bell Labs, and was part of the team that developed Ubiquitous Computing at PARC. He is Associate Editor-in-Chief of Computer Magazine and a past member of the Board of Governors of the IEEE Computer Society. Bill received a Ph.D. from Columbia University in 1995.
fields.name: Google Tech Talk

fields.description: Amin Vahdat is an alumnus of UC Berkeley with a BS in EECS and a PhD in Computer Science.  He is also a member of the Berkeley chapter of both Eta Kappa Nu and Tau Beta Pi.  Vahdat is now a Professor and in the Department of Computer Science and Engineering at the University of California San Diego, where he is also the Director of UCSD's Center for Networked Systems. His research interests lie broadly in computer systems, including networking, distributed systems, mobility, and operating systems.  He has run graduate admissions at UCSD for the last four years and will speak about his own perspectives in applying to graduate programs and what admissions committees look for in evaluating applicants.

It's time for the famous photo scavenger hunt!

Meet at the Woz! We'll divide you into groups and give you a set of clues. Take your digital camera with you and get ready to run around the campus looking for the perfect pictures! After all the workouts, enjoy BBQ with us!

Don't forget your umbrella!

Location: the Woz!!

Meet HMC 7 PM for rides. (Don't forget to bring some $$!)

PS: No food will be served. Please ignore the "Free Pizza" in the RSVP list =D

fields.description:
Every year Cal Day is the campus-wide open house for UC Berkeley, and HKN helps out giving tours of Soda and Cory and staffing the information tables.  So come show off your knowledge of the EECS department and its headquarters to prospective students and people interested in Cal. Sign up for an hour slot, but remember only THREE candidates per hour. Tours will be leaving every 20 minutes.

Location: Inside Cory Hall Entrance
fields.name: Cal Day

fields.description:
Enjoy a lovely dinner with HKN Alumni, Officers, Members, and Candidates. Meet old friends and make new ones! Alumni Appreciation Dinner this year will be at PF Chang's in Emeryville at 8:30pm. An email was sent out with information about the the menu!

Make sure you bring some money with you as HKN will not reimburse you for this.

Location:
PF Chang's in Emeryville
5633 Bay Street
Emeryville, CA 94608

Time: Dinner is at 8:30pm. Meet at 7:30pm at HMC for rides. Please be on time!

Menu: Please see email for details about the menu! This is important!
fields.name: Alumni Appreciation Dinner

Come out and play Ultimate Frisbee against TBP!

Location: North Field (its next to Barrows Hall)
fields.name: Ultimate Frisbee

fields.description:
Leave all your homework behind tonight and join us in some video and board games. Work out some mid-semester frustrations by totally pwning in Halo 3.  You're welcome to bring any kinds of games you have! Remember, the more the merrier ;)

Location: the Woz!

fields.description:
It's the middle of the semester already and it's time for the 2nd GM! Candidates, make sure you can make it. You wouldn't wanna miss the chance to hang out with us, would you? =D

As always, delicious dinner will be provided!

Location: the Woz

Here it comes.. the most awaited activity of the semester. 
It's the Officers and Members vs. Alumni and Candidates broomball showdown!!

Make sure you can make it! Bring your game face. It's gonna be wild.

Meet at 8:45PM at HMC for rides.


Location:
Oakland Ice Center
519 18th Street
Oakland, CA 94612

Time: Meet at 8:45pm for rides. Broomball starts at 9:45pm.

fields.description:

Meet at HMC at 7PM for rides

fields.description:
Meander up a moonlit path to the iconic Big C.  Look over the nighttime scenery of the city lights around the bay as you bask in the glorious light of the full moon.    

Meet at HMC. We'll walk together from there!
fields.name: Big C Hike

HKN will only reimburse $4/person so make sure you bring extra money =)

Location: Fenton's Creamery, Oakland
